courses.learning_outcomes:
After taking this course, students are expected to master the basic writing, reading, and communication skills such as:
(1) the pronunciations, marks and writings of Arabic letters;
(2) greetings in Islamic way and normal way;
(3) exchanging basic personal information with someone in a social occasion;
(4) describing an object, shopping, making an appointment, offering help, and describing food.

Upon successful completion of the course, students will have acquired the ability to:
• read Arabic texts containing high frequency lexis and basic structures;
• understand basic conversations or understand the gist of more complex conversations dealing with familiar topics;
• talk on familiar and simple topics with reasonable fluency;
• ask for information, make suggestions and make requests fairly confidently;
• write a short personal text or letter about familiar subjects.
By the end of the course, students should be able to perform at Level A1.2 of the Common European Framework.

Upon successful completion of the course, students should be able to:
• comprehend short conversations about most survival needs and limited social demands;
• initiate and maintain predictable face-to-face conversations and satisfy limited social demands such as travel and accommodation needs;
• understand most factual material in non-technical prose;
• use the linguistic context and real-world knowledge to make sensible guesses about unfamiliar material;
• write routine social correspondence and short texts related to daily situations.
By the end of the course, students should be able to perform at Level A1 of the Common European Framework.

